data.title: TV Schedule for WUPA Atlanta, GA
data.meta_description: Check out today's TV schedule for WUPA Atlanta, GA and take a look at what is scheduled for the next 2 weeks.
data.text:
Two and a Half Men Back Off Mary Poppins

Alan learns that Charlie belongs to an exclusive men's group, and he begs his brother to let him join.

Two and a Half Men Yay, No Polyps!

Charlie undergoes a colonoscopy to avoid a trip to see Chelsea's bigoted parents, but he finds them in his living room when he returns home.

American Housewife American Idol

Greg enlists Oliver and Anna-Kat's help to drum up new recruits for the Westport Historical Guild; Katie does her best to support Taylor's dreams of becoming the next "American Idol."

American Housewife Insta-Friends

Katie feels left out when Greg becomes fast friends with the newest member of the Westport Historical Guild; Oliver fears Cooper is ditching him when he sees on social media that Cooper lied about his weekend plans.

Family Guy Boy (Dog) Meets Girl (Dog)

Brian is smitten with a female show dog and enters a show dog competition in which the winner gets to breed her; Peter and Lois go to extreme measures to try to convince Chris that Arthur Valentine doesn't exist.

Bob's Burgers My Fuzzy Valentine

The kids talk Bob into letting them cut school so they can help him select a Valentine's Day gift for Linda; Linda organizes a speed-dating event at the restaurant.

Dr. Phil Aaron Hernandez's Fiancee Addresses the Rumors

Dr. Phil's exclusive interview continues with the fiancee of former football star Aaron Hernandez: Shayanna Jenkins-Hernandez responds to questions about his sexuality and rumored relationship with a fellow inmate.

Jerry Springer Sexxxy Strippers

While stripper Alex was on maternity leave, her customer Raymond accepted dances from one of her colleagues; Jessica wants to break up her cousin's relationship; Jerry and some audience members must help Savannah decide which woman to take with her.

Creflo Dollar

Dr. Creflo Dollar ministers to people from all backgrounds with hopes for change; Creflo helps viewers find ways to renew their faith, mind, and spirit; Creflo and his wife Taffi share their vision for everyone to understand God's love and promises.

Top Secret Files: Declassified

Investigating some of the government's most infamous mysteries using interviews, reenactments, archival footage and access to years of top secret FBI files.

The Drew Barrymore Show Arthur Brooks

Drew continues her chat with author Arthur Brooks (podcast "The Art of Happiness") about the science behind worrying and some of the biggest things people worry about.

People Puzzler Love Is All Around

Three contestants put their pop culture knowledge to the test to complete crosswords based on the iconic puzzles in People magazine.

People Puzzler Life of the Party

Three contestants put their pop culture knowledge to the test to complete crosswords based on the iconic puzzles in People magazine.

Lauren Lake's Paternity Court Reaves vs. Silva

A Florida man says it's OK for men to cheat on their wives, and now he's in court claiming his girlfriend cheated and another man is her son's father.

Lauren Lake's Paternity Court Richardson vs. Robbins

A Minnesota man claims his ex-girlfriend is still married and believes her husband is the father of her two-month-old son.

America's Court With Judge Ross Lash Extension & Who Needs Friends

A salon owner fails to reimburse an employee for taking an eyelash course as promised; the cost of car repairs comes between friends.

America's Court With Judge Ross Very Neighborly & A Storm Is Brewing

Vandalism after an affair is discovered; a laptop and a cup of coffee lead to a dispute between college students.

Cutlers Court Holland vs. Bryant

Breon issues his girlfriend, Chenika, an ultimatum regarding her refusal to have another baby and grow their family of nine to 10.

Couples Court With the Cutlers Wilder vs. Wilder

A man from Georgia regrets opening Pandora's box by bringing another couple into his marriage.

Couples Court With the Cutlers Nelson vs. Nelson

A Georgia man becomes determined to prove his faithfulness and win back his ex-wife.

Judge Mathis

Plaintiff became a ward of the state at age 4 and at age 12, ran away to become a prostitute; she says she turned her life around and started dating the defendant, but he was unfaithful and also a cocaine abuser; she claims he vandalized her car.
